# Pod Security Audit

This review lists Pod Security controls to compare against the generated Deployment and any future Helm chart values.

## Recommended controls

- `runAsNonRoot: true`
- explicit `runAsUser` when the image supports it
- `allowPrivilegeEscalation: false`
- `readOnlyRootFilesystem: true` when writable paths are not required
- `capabilities.drop: ["ALL"]`
- `seccompProfile` set to `RuntimeDefault`
- no `hostNetwork`
- no `hostPID`
- no `hostIPC`
- no privileged container
- CPU and memory resources defined

## Manual validation

These controls must be reviewed in the rendered manifests and in any runtime admission policy. This readiness file does not inspect a live Pod and does not enforce Pod Security admission.
